<title>USA: Novell negotiates $1.3 mln settlements.</title>
<headline>Novell negotiates $1.3 mln settlements.</headline>
<dateline>PROVO, Utah 1997-06-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Novell Inc said Wednesday it negotiated legal settlements worth about $1.3 million.</p>
<p>Most of the settlements involved complaints of companies who were selling upgraded NetWare and IntranetWare as new product to unsuspecting customers, the company said.</p>
<p>Novell said it settled with computer resellers Jaco Electronics Inc, Micro Supply, Accord Systems, Digidrive, RTI and the individuals Fatemah Asadi and Vajiholah Sabet.</p>
<p>The company said the terms of the individual settlements were confidential.</p>
